57rtc::scoped_refptr<PeerConnectionFactoryInterface>
58CreateModularPeerConnectionFactory(
59 PeerConnectionFactoryDependencies dependencies) {
60 // The PeerConnectionFactory must be created on the signaling thread.
61 if (dependencies.signaling_thread &&
62 !dependencies.signaling_thread->IsCurrent()) {
63 return dependencies.signaling_thread
64 ->Invoke<rtc::scoped_refptr<PeerConnectionFactoryInterface>>(
65 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&dependencies] {
66 return CreateModularPeerConnectionFactory(
67 std::move(dependencies));
68 });
69 }
70
71 auto pc_factory = PeerConnectionFactory::Create(std::move(dependencies));
72 if (!pc_factory) {
73 return nullptr;
74 }
75 // Verify that the invocation and the initialization ended up agreeing on the
76 // thread.
77 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(pc_factory->signaling_thread());
78 return PeerConnectionFactoryProxy::Create(
79 pc_factory->signaling_thread(), pc_factory->worker_thread(), pc_factory);
80}
81
82// Static
83rtc::scoped_refptr<PeerConnectionFactory> PeerConnectionFactory::Create(
84 PeerConnectionFactoryDependencies dependencies) {
85 auto context = ConnectionContext::Create(&dependencies);
86 if (!context) {
87 return nullptr;
88 }
89 return rtc::make_ref_counted<PeerConnectionFactory>(context, &dependencies);
90}

92PeerConnectionFactory::PeerConnectionFactory(
93 rtc::scoped_refptr<ConnectionContext> context,
94 PeerConnectionFactoryDependencies* dependencies)
95 : context_(context),
96 task_queue_factory_(std::move(dependencies->task_queue_factory)),
97 event_log_factory_(std::move(dependencies->event_log_factory)),
98 fec_controller_factory_(std::move(dependencies->fec_controller_factory)),
99 network_state_predictor_factory_(
100 std::move(dependencies->network_state_predictor_factory)),
101 injected_network_controller_factory_(
102 std::move(dependencies->network_controller_factory)),
103 neteq_factory_(std::move(dependencies->neteq_factory)) {}
104
105PeerConnectionFactory::PeerConnectionFactory(
106 PeerConnectionFactoryDependencies dependencies)
107 : PeerConnectionFactory(ConnectionContext::Create(&dependencies),
108 &dependencies) {}

110PeerConnectionFactory::~PeerConnectionFactory() {
111 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
112}

119RtpCapabilities PeerConnectionFactory::GetRtpSenderCapabilities(
120 cricket::MediaType kind) const {
121 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
122 switch (kind) {
123 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO: {
124 cricket::AudioCodecs cricket_codecs;
125 channel_manager()->GetSupportedAudioSendCodecs(&cricket_codecs);
126 return ToRtpCapabilities(
127 cricket_codecs,
128 channel_manager()->GetDefaultEnabledAudioRtpHeaderExtensions());
129 }
130 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO: {
131 cricket::VideoCodecs cricket_codecs;
132 channel_manager()->GetSupportedVideoSendCodecs(&cricket_codecs);
133 return ToRtpCapabilities(
134 cricket_codecs,
135 channel_manager()->GetDefaultEnabledVideoRtpHeaderExtensions());
136 }
137 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
138 return RtpCapabilities();
139 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED:
140 return RtpCapabilities();
141 }
142 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
143}
144

189RTCErrorOr<rtc::scoped_refptr<PeerConnectionInterface>>
190PeerConnectionFactory::CreatePeerConnectionOrError(
191 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& configuration,
192 PeerConnectionDependencies dependencies) {
193 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
194 RTC_DCHECK(!(dependencies.allocator && dependencies.packet_socket_factory))
195 << "You can't set both allocator and packet_socket_factory; "
196 "the former is going away (see bugs.webrtc.org/7447";
197
198 // Set internal defaults if optional dependencies are not set.
199 if (!dependencies.cert_generator) {
200 dependencies.cert_generator =
201 std::make_unique<rtc::RTCCertificateGenerator>(signaling_thread(),
202 network_thread());
203 }
204 if (!dependencies.allocator) {
205 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* packet_socket_factory;
206 if (dependencies.packet_socket_factory)
207 packet_socket_factory = dependencies.packet_socket_factory.get();
208 else
209 packet_socket_factory = context_->default_socket_factory();
210
211 dependencies.allocator = std::make_unique<cricket::BasicPortAllocator>(
212 context_->default_network_manager(), packet_socket_factory,
213 configuration.turn_customizer);
214 }
215
216 if (!dependencies.async_resolver_factory) {
217 dependencies.async_resolver_factory =
218 std::make_unique<webrtc::BasicAsyncResolverFactory>();
219 }
220
221 if (!dependencies.ice_transport_factory) {
222 dependencies.ice_transport_factory =
223 std::make_unique<DefaultIceTransportFactory>();
224 }
225
226 dependencies.allocator->SetNetworkIgnoreMask(options().network_ignore_mask);
227
228 std::unique_ptr<RtcEventLog> event_log =
229 worker_thread()->Invoke<std::unique_ptr<RtcEventLog>>(
230 RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] { return CreateRtcEventLog_w(); });
231
232 std::unique_ptr<Call> call = worker_thread()->Invoke<std::unique_ptr<Call>>(
233 RTC_FROM_HERE,
234 [this, &event_log] { return CreateCall_w(event_log.get()); });
235
236 auto result = PeerConnection::Create(context_, options_, std::move(event_log),
237 std::move(call), configuration,
238 std::move(dependencies));
239 if (!result.ok()) {
240 return result.MoveError();
241 }
242 // We configure the proxy with a pointer to the network thread for methods
243 // that need to be invoked there rather than on the signaling thread.
244 // Internally, the proxy object has a member variable named |worker_thread_|
245 // which will point to the network thread (and not the factory's
246 // worker_thread()). All such methods have thread checks though, so the code
247 // should still be clear (outside of macro expansion).
248 rtc::scoped_refptr<PeerConnectionInterface> result_proxy =
249 PeerConnectionProxy::Create(signaling_thread(), network_thread(),
250 result.MoveValue());
251 return result_proxy;
252}

261rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoTrackInterface> PeerConnectionFactory::CreateVideoTrack(
262 const std::string& id,
263 VideoTrackSourceInterface* source) {
264 RTC_DCHECK(signaling_thread()->IsCurrent());
265 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoTrackInterface> track(
266 VideoTrack::Create(id, source, worker_thread()));
267 return VideoTrackProxy::Create(signaling_thread(), worker_thread(), track);
268}

282std::unique_ptr<RtcEventLog> PeerConnectionFactory::CreateRtcEventLog_w() {
283 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
284
285 auto encoding_type = RtcEventLog::EncodingType::Legacy;
286 if (IsTrialEnabled("WebRTC-RtcEventLogNewFormat"))
287 encoding_type = RtcEventLog::EncodingType::NewFormat;
288 return event_log_factory_
289 ? event_log_factory_->CreateRtcEventLog(encoding_type)
290 : std::make_unique<RtcEventLogNull>();
291}
292
293std::unique_ptr<Call> PeerConnectionFactory::CreateCall_w(
294 RtcEventLog* event_log) {
295 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
296
297 webrtc::Call::Config call_config(event_log, network_thread());
298 if (!channel_manager()->media_engine() || !context_->call_factory()) {
299 return nullptr;
300 }
301 call_config.audio_state =
302 channel_manager()->media_engine()->voice().GetAudioState();
303
304 FieldTrialParameter<DataRate> min_bandwidth("min",
305 DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(30));
306 FieldTrialParameter<DataRate> start_bandwidth("start",
307 DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(300));
308 FieldTrialParameter<DataRate> max_bandwidth("max",
309 DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(2000));
310 ParseFieldTrial({&min_bandwidth, &start_bandwidth, &max_bandwidth},
311 trials().Lookup("WebRTC-PcFactoryDefaultBitrates"));
312
313 call_config.bitrate_config.min_bitrate_bps =
314 rtc::saturated_cast<int>(min_bandwidth->bps());
315 call_config.bitrate_config.start_bitrate_bps =
316 rtc::saturated_cast<int>(start_bandwidth->bps());
317 call_config.bitrate_config.max_bitrate_bps =
318 rtc::saturated_cast<int>(max_bandwidth->bps());
319
320 call_config.fec_controller_factory = fec_controller_factory_.get();
321 call_config.task_queue_factory = task_queue_factory_.get();
322 call_config.network_state_predictor_factory =
323 network_state_predictor_factory_.get();
324 call_config.neteq_factory = neteq_factory_.get();
325
326 if (IsTrialEnabled("WebRTC-Bwe-InjectedCongestionController")) {
327 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Using injected network controller factory";
328 call_config.network_controller_factory =
329 injected_network_controller_factory_.get();
330 } else {
331 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Using default network controller factory";
332 }
333
334 call_config.trials = &trials();
335
336 return std::unique_ptr<Call>(
337 context_->call_factory()->CreateCall(call_config));
338}
339
340bool PeerConnectionFactory::IsTrialEnabled(absl::string_view key) const {
341 return absl::StartsWith(trials().Lookup(key), "Enabled");
342}
